<title>SINGAPORE: Microsoft, NEC in Internet hotel venture.</title>
<headline>Microsoft, NEC in Internet hotel venture.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-05-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>U.S. software giant Microsoft Corp and Japanese computer maker NEC Corp said on Tuesday they launched an Internet computer service for hotels.</p>
<p>Microsoft said in a statement the venture, involving an investment of Singapore $30 million (US$21 million) over two to three years, would install personal computers in every room in a series of hotels in Singapore and the region.</p>
<p>The venture, HotelNet, would use NEC computers running on Microsoft software, NEC said in a statement.</p>
<p>Three Singapore hotels had installed the new service and other hotels in Manila, Japan and Malaysia would soon follow.  </p>
<p>In a separate statement, news and information company Reuters Holdings Ltd said it would be the main provider of news on HotelNet. The news would be available in English and Japanese.</p>
<p>--Singapore Newsroom (+65-870-3199)</p>
<p>($1 = S$1.43)</p>
